<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<worksheet>
  <title>GR-1 Quadratic Functions and Models</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      <alert>Instructions:</alert> Once you open the quiz, your timer begins.  I would recommend having an additional timer
        that goes off about 5 minutes prior, so that you know when to start uploading your work.
    </p>
    <p> Write out complete solutions to the following problems.</p>
  </introduction>

  <page>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Given the function <m>f(x)=-3x^2+12x-9</m>.
          <ol>
            <li>Write the function in vertex form.</li>
            <li>State the intercepts.</li>
            <li>State the range.</li>
            <li>Graph f(x).</li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>A gardener has 340ft of fencing to fence a garden alongside 
          the house (the side against the house will not be fenced).  The 
          gardener wants to use some of the fencing running perpendicular 
          to the house to create two equal sized plots. What dimensions 
          are needed to create the largest plots.
        <ol>
          <li>Define the variable for your function.</li>
          <li>Set up the quadratic model.</li>
          <li>State the practical domain.</li>
          <li>Find the dimensions that maximize the area.</li>
        </ol>
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>
